From: Andrew Lennon <andrew.lennon@dynamicdevices.co.uk>
Date: Tue, 19 May 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ASoC: tas6424: rename mixer controls for passenger tannoys

TI upstream labels the DAC volume kcontrols "Speaker Driver CHn", which is
easily confused with the cab driver speaker (TAS2563) on DT510. Rename to
"Tannoy CHn" so amixer/alsamixer match product terminology (tannoys mixer).

Signed-off-by: Andrew Lennon <andrew.lennon@dynamicdevices.co.uk>
---
 sound/soc/codecs/tas6424.c | 8 ++++----
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/codecs/tas6424.c b/sound/soc/codecs/tas6424.c
index 1111111..2222222 100644
--- a/sound/soc/codecs/tas6424.c
+++ b/sound/soc/codecs/tas6424.c
@@ -58,11 +58,11 @@ static const struct snd_kcontrol_new tas6424_snd_controls[] = {
 static const struct snd_kcontrol_new tas6424_snd_controls[] = {
-	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Speaker Driver CH1 Playback Volume",
+	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Tannoy CH1 Playback Volume",
 		       TAS6424_CH1_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0, dac_tlv),
-	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Speaker Driver CH2 Playback Volume",
+	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Tannoy CH2 Playback Volume",
 		       TAS6424_CH2_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0, dac_tlv),
-	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Speaker Driver CH3 Playback Volume",
+	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Tannoy CH3 Playback Volume",
 		       TAS6424_CH3_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0, dac_tlv),
-	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Speaker Driver CH4 Playback Volume",
+	SOC_SINGLE_TLV("Tannoy CH4 Playback Volume",
 		       TAS6424_CH4_VOL_CTRL, 0, 0xff, 0, dac_tlv),
 	SOC_SINGLE_STROBE("Auto Diagnostics Switch", TAS6424_DC_DIAG_CTRL1,
 			  TAS6424_LDGBYPASS_SHIFT, 1),
